          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "EC3Membership_UserHasBudgetAccess",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to determine if a user, identified by their email address, has access to budget-related functionalities within a system. It checks if the user is active, in use, and belongs to specific roles ('Administrator' or 'SeniorAdministrator'). The procedure outputs a boolean value indicating whether the user is authenticated for budget access."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
